{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox company | name = Masterclass.com | image = Masterclass logo.svg | website = {{url|masterclass.com}} | genre = Online tutorials | founded = 2014 }}
'''MasterClass''' is a San Francisco-based online education platform. Students can access tutorials and lectures pre-recorded by experts in various fields.
== Production == The concept was conceived by David Rogier and [[Aaron Rasmussen]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/02/23/masterclass-raises-15-million-for-online-classes-taught-by-celebrities/|title=MasterClass Raises $15 Million For Online Classes Taught By Celebrities|last=Loizos|first=Connie|work=TechCrunch|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref>
== Content == In addition to the video classes, class workbook and homework are also part of the course. In the case of actor [[Dustin Hoffman]]'s course, the "interactive assignments" involved the student acting with other students, either in person or over [[Skype]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/dustin-hoffmans-online-acting-class-what-its-like-to-learn-from-the-master-10285753.html|title=Dustin Hoffman's online acting class: What it's like to learn from the master|date=May 29, 2015|work=The Independent|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref>
== Critical reception == The general consensus among critics is that while the classes do not teach technical skills to improve proficiency in the craft, they provide insight into the grueling nature of artistic pursuits and striving for perfection while inspiring a love of the craft.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/christina-aguileras-masterclass-singing-review-892349|title=Christina Aguilera's MasterClass in Singing Through the Eyes of a Non-Singer|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-master-class-steve-martin-kevin-spacey-20170714-story.html|title=In this digital self-help age, just how effective are MasterClass's A-list celebrity workshops?|first=Amy|last=Kaufman|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=July 14, 2017|accessdate=May 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://au.askmen.com/fine_living/wine_dine_archive/gordon-ramsay-masterclass-review.html|title=Can Gordon Ramsay's MasterClass Make You A Master Chef? We Tried It|last=Osburn|first=Christopher|work=AskMen|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.refinery29.com/2015/08/92007/dustin-hoffman-masterclass-acting-review|title=What It's Like To Take An Acting Class With Dustin Hoffman|publisher=[[Refinery29]]|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://observer.com/2015/08/an-accomplished-writer-takes-a-master-class-from-a-gargantuan-selling-writer/|title=An Accomplished Writer Takes a ‘MasterClass’ From a Gargantuan Selling Writer|date=August 4, 2015|work=Observer|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vulture.com/2015/12/masterclass-on-art-of-performance-with-usher.html|title=What I Learned From Usher’s Online Class on ‘the Art of Performance’|date=December 29, 2015|work=Vulture|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref>
''[[The Verge]]'' noted that while the subscriptions last a lifetime, each course has little replay value, and so it is challenging to keep the student learning within the platform once they have viewed the video classes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/5/15/15640354/masterclass-users-werner-herzog-gordon-ramsay|title=Who is MasterClass for? Talking to the people who take online classes with big-name celebs|work=The Verge|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref> Reviewopedia noted that while there are many educational tutorial platforms, this has a point of difference as having teachers that are worldwide recognised in their fields.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reviewopedia.com/masterclass-com-reviews|title=MasterClass.com Reviews - Legit or Scam?|publisher=Reviewopedia|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref> ''[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]'' noted that the classes are not interactive, which is a symptom of online courses in general.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/david-mamet-masterclass-tutorial-playwriting-screenwriting-1202072976/|title=David Mamet Teaches Master Class On Writing For Stage & Screen|last=Fleming|first=Mike Jr|date=April 20, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=December 27, 2017}}</ref>
[[Kevin Spacey]]'s and [[Dustin Hoffman]]'s acting courses were removed in late 2017 after multiple sexual assault allegations had come out against both actors.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2017/10/kevin-spacey-masterclass-dropped-from-online-video-hub-1202198664/|title=Kevin Spacey MasterClass Dropped From Online Instructional Video Hub|last=Hayes|first=Dade|date=October 31, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=April 1, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>
