'''Norfolk leather cases''' were [[luggage]] made in the 1940s and 1950s for business and domestic applications. They came in a range of sizes from [[suitcase]]s to a much smaller [[attaché case]]. Norfolk cases were made of moulded [[leather]] that resulted in cases with no cut or sewn corners.{{sfn|Gulshan|2003|page=160}}

